.TH MRPD 8 "2026-07-15" "OpenSRP" "System Manager's Manual"
.SH NAME
mrpd \- Multiple Registration Protocol / Stream Reservation Protocol daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mrpd
.B \-b
.I bridge
.RB [ \-\-enable\-srp ]
.RB [ \-\-enable\-mmrp ]
.RB [ \-\-enable\-mvrp ]
.RB [ \-\-enable\-msrp ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mrpd
(OpenSRP) is an implementation of the IEEE 802.1Q Stream Reservation Protocol
(SRP) suite: the Multiple MAC Registration Protocol (MMRP), the Multiple VLAN
Registration Protocol (MVRP) and the Multiple Stream Reservation Protocol
(MSRP). These protocols are applications of the generalized Multiple
Registration Protocol (MRP, 802.1Q clause 10) and are used in AVB/TSN networks
to coordinate multicast group membership, VLAN membership and stream bandwidth
reservations amongst Ethernet bridges.
.PP
.B mrpd
runs on a Linux bridge and drives the standard kernel interfaces: it installs
forwarding database (FDB/MDB) entries for registered groups and streams,
manages VLAN membership, and adjusts the Credit Based Shaper (CBS) traffic
control parameters dynamically as reservations come and go (when no streams are
reserved the
.B cbs
qdisc is replaced by the default
.BR pfifo_fast ).
It acts as the sole MRP entity on the bridge, running the applicant, registrar
and attribute\-propagation state machines itself on behalf of every managed
port.
.PP
At least one application protocol must be enabled (see
.B APPLICATION PROTOCOLS
below); enabling none leaves the daemon idle. A master bridge interface
.RB ( \-b )
is required.
.PP
.B mrpd
integrates with
.BR systemd :
when run as a service it logs to the journal and issues readiness/stop
notifications; otherwise it logs to standard error. It shuts down gracefully on
.B SIGTERM
and
.BR SIGINT .
.SH APPLICATION PROTOCOLS
.TP
.B \-\-enable\-srp
Convenience switch enabling the full Stream Reservation Protocol suite: it
turns on MVRP and MSRP (and turns MMRP off). This is the normal way to run the
daemon for AVB/TSN.
.TP
.B \-\-enable\-mmrp
Enable the Multiple MAC Registration Protocol (multicast group registration).
.TP
.B \-\-enable\-mvrp
Enable the Multiple VLAN Registration Protocol (VLAN membership registration).
.TP
.B \-\-enable\-msrp
Enable the Multiple Stream Reservation Protocol (stream bandwidth reservation).
MSRP relies on MVRP for VLAN propagation, so it is normally enabled alongside
it (as
.B \-\-enable\-srp
does).
.SH OPTIONS
.SS General
.TP
.BI \-b ", " \-\-bridge\-interface " name"
Master bridge interface name (required), e.g.
.BR br0 .
.TP
.BI \-q ", " \-\-q\-disc\-handle " handle"
Root qdisc handle used when installing traffic control queues. Default
.BR 0x9000 .
.TP
.BI \-\-exclude\-iface " name"
Exclude a physical interface from MRP processing. May be given more than once.
.TP
.BI \-\-exclude\-vlan " vid"
Exclude a VLAN from MVRP declaration/propagation. May be given more than once.
.TP
.BI \-l ", " \-\-log\-level " level"
Logging verbosity: one of
.BR trace ", " debug ", " info ", " notice ", " warning ", " error ", " critical .
Default
.BR info .
.TP
.B \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SS gPTP / AVB capability
.TP
.B \-\-ignore\-as\-capable ", " \-\-no\-ignore\-as\-capable
Whether to ignore the gPTP
.I asCapable
status of a port (and skip querying PTP for it). Enabled by default; pass
.B \-\-no\-ignore\-as\-capable
to enforce 802.1Q 35.2.1, gating MSRP participation on a port that is gPTP
capable. See also
.BR \-\-pmc\-uds\-path .
.TP
.B \-\-force\-avb\-capable
Force all ports to advertise as AVB capable regardless of their actual
capability.
.SS PTP management client
.TP
.BI \-\-pmc\-uds\-path " path"
UNIX domain socket path of the PTP management client, used to query per\-port
.I asCapable
state from the local gPTP daemon (e.g.
.BR ptp4l ).
Relevant only when
.B \-\-no\-ignore\-as\-capable
is in effect.
.SS MSRP behaviour
.TP
.B \-\-enable\-talker\-pruning
Enable MSRP talker pruning: do not propagate a Talker declaration out ports on
which no matching Listener has registered.
.TP
.B \-\-leave\-immediate ", " \-\-no\-leave\-immediate
Whether the registrar leaves immediately on a received Leave, rather than
waiting for the LeaveTimer to expire. Enabled by default per Avnu ProAV Bridge
Specification section 9.2; pass
.B \-\-no\-leave\-immediate
to restore the standard 802.1Q leave timing.
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-fan\-in\-ports " n"
Maximum number of MSRP fan\-in ports (ports from which Talker declarations may
be accepted).
.B 0
(the default) means no limit.
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-talker\-attributes " n"
Global limit on the number of MSRP Talker attributes registered across all
ports (Avnu ProAV Bridge Specification section 9.3). A Talker declaration beyond
the limit is ignored. Default
.BR 150 ;
.B 0
disables the limit.
.TP
.BI \-\-sr\-p\-vid " vid"
The SR PVID: the single VLAN that both SR classes declare in their MSRP Domain
(802.1Q 35.2.1.4). Default
.BR 2 .
.SS Traffic class queues and bandwidth
.TP
.BI \-\-class\-a\-qdisc\-handle " n"
Egress queue (qdisc handle) for SR class A traffic. Default
.BR 4 .
.TP
.BI \-\-class\-b\-qdisc\-handle " n"
Egress queue (qdisc handle) for SR class B traffic. Default
.BR 3 .
.TP
.BI \-\-class\-a\-delta\-bandwidth " percent"
SR class A delta bandwidth, as a percentage. If unset, an implementation
default is used.
.TP
.BI \-\-class\-b\-delta\-bandwidth " percent"
SR class B delta bandwidth, as a percentage. If unset, an implementation
default is used.
.TP
.B \-\-configure\-egress\-queues
Automatically configure the MQPRIO egress queues.
.TP
.B \-\-configure\-ingress\-queues
Automatically configure the DCBNL ingress queue (PCP) mapping.
.TP
.B \-\-configure\-queues
Automatically configure both ingress and egress queues (equivalent to giving
both of the two options above).
.TP
.B \-\-configure\-ingress\-mdb
Install an MDB entry on the Talker's ingress port. This enables "secure switch"
mode, where the ingress port also requires a dynamic reservation entry to admit
an SR stream to the AVB queues.
.TP
.B \-\-configure\-nft\-drop , \-\-no\-configure\-nft\-drop
Install (the default) or omit a pre-routing nftables hook that drops the enabled
applications' MMRP/MVRP group addresses, so the bridge does not flood them;
.B mrpd
snoops and propagates these frames itself. The table is owned by
.BR mrpd 's
netlink socket, so the kernel removes it when
.B mrpd
exits. See
.B USAGE NOTES
below.
.TP
.BI \-\-configure\-filtering " type"
Enable per-port AVB admission control on each AVB-capable bridge port, using the
given mechanism. Two
.I type
values are supported.
.RS
.TP
.B marvell
Set the mv88e6xxx per-port AVB ingress mode through the
.B avb_cfg
devlink parameter: secure mode when
.B \-\-configure\-ingress\-mdb
is also given, otherwise enhanced (reservation-checked) mode. Ports are returned
to the default legacy mode on teardown.
.TP
.B tcflower
Install
.BR tc (8)
cls_flower ingress rules on the port's
.B clsact
qdisc, for use with a software (non-offloaded) bridge: on in-domain ports drop
SR-priority frames lacking a dynamic reservation, and on boundary ports
regenerate SR-priority frames to priority 0. Requires a kernel with cls_flower
and the dynamic-reservation match key; boundary regeneration acts on the
in-payload VLAN tag only.
.RE
.PP
A class is filtered only once the port has joined that SR class's domain. Ports
left unconfigured keep the switch default.
.SS MVRP behaviour
.TP
.B \-\-declare\-pvid ", " \-\-no\-declare\-pvid
Whether to declare each port's PVID over MVRP (802.1Q 11.2.1.3). Disabled by
default; pass
.B \-\-declare\-pvid
to advertise the port VLAN identifier as well as the statically configured
tagged VLANs.
.SS MRP timers
All timer intervals are given in seconds (fractional values are accepted).
.TP
.BI \-\-join\-time " seconds"
MRP JoinTime interval. Default
.BR 0.2 .
.TP
.BI \-\-leave\-time " seconds"
MRP LeaveTime interval. Default
.BR 5.0 .
.TP
.BI \-\-leave\-all\-time " seconds"
MRP LeaveAllTime interval. Default
.BR 10.0 .
.TP
.BI \-\-periodic\-time " seconds"
MRP PeriodicTransmission interval;
.B 0
disables periodic transmission. Default
.BR 1.0 .
Enabled by default for robust interoperability with peers using a short
LeaveTime (802.1Q 10.7.2).
.SS REST management (optional)
.TP
.BI \-r ", " \-\-rest\-server\-port " port"
TCP port for the built\-in REST management HTTP server. Available only when
.B mrpd
was built with the
.B RestAPI
trait; if absent, the REST server is not compiled in.
.SH USAGE NOTES
.B mrpd
expects the bridge, its member interfaces, VLANs and base traffic control
qdiscs to be configured beforehand with standard tools such as
.BR ip (8),
.BR bridge (8)
and
.BR tc (8).
A pre\-routing
.BR nftables (8)
drop hook for MMRP/MVRP frames (destination
.B 01:80:c2:00:00:20
and
.BR 01:80:c2:00:00:21 )
stops the bridge flooding them;
.B mrpd
snoops these frames itself over an ingress raw
.RB ( AF_PACKET )
socket and propagates them. By default
.B mrpd
installs this hook itself in an owner\-scoped nftables table that the kernel
removes when the daemon exits; pass
.B \-\-no\-configure\-nft\-drop
to configure it out\-of\-band instead.
.PP
Where an STP daemon is present,
.B mrpd
polls
.BR mstpd (8)
over its control socket for each port's spanning\-tree role, using it to drive
MRP topology\-change processing (Flush!/Re\-declare!). Bridges without
.B mstpd
simply skip this.
.PP
Do not run a second MVRP applicant against a bridge port managed by
.BR mrpd :
neither the Linux in\-kernel 8021q MVRP applicant stacked over a managed port,
nor a separate MVRP daemon. The kernel applicant remains the correct way for a
Linux
.I end station
(a peer on the far end of a link) to declare membership toward the bridge.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM ", " SIGINT
Initiate a graceful shutdown (deregister and tear down state).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/default/avb
Default environment file read by the
.B systemd
service unit (bridge name, interface/group lists and
.B MRPD_OPTS
extra options).
.SH EXAMPLES
Run the full SRP suite on bridge
.BR br0 ,
configuring egress queues and secure\-switch ingress MDB entries:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
mrpd --enable-srp -b br0 --configure-egress-queues --configure-ingress-mdb
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run MVRP only, excluding the management VLAN and an uplink interface:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
mrpd --enable-mvrp -b br0 --exclude-vlan 1 --exclude-iface eth0
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bridge (8),
.BR ip (8),
.BR tc (8),
.BR nft (8),
.BR mstpd (8),
.BR ptp4l (8)
.PP
IEEE Std 802.1Q (clauses 10, 11, 35), IEEE Std 802.1BA, and the Avnu ProAV
Bridge Specification.
